{% macro delivery_generic(delivery) -%}
{% if delivery.name == "sandbox" -%}
Write final output files under `{{ output_path(delivery, "") }}` using their workspace-relative layout. For example, workspace file `results.jsonl` belongs at `{{ output_path(delivery, "results.jsonl") }}`, and `nested/out.txt` belongs at `{{ output_path(delivery, "nested/out.txt") }}`. Only files under that output root are collected.
{% elif delivery.name == "share" -%}
Write final output files under `{{ output_path(delivery, "") }}`, then share each final file exactly once through the endpoint file-share mechanism. Each shared file must carry a recoverable path below `{{ output_path(delivery, "") }}`; endpoint-specific details define the path identity format. Do not share scratch files or paste file contents.
{% elif delivery.name == "stdout" -%}
Write final output files under `{{ output_path(delivery, "") }}`, then emit each final file exactly once with a separate shell command whose entire command text is `cat <path>`. Do not combine that `cat` with writes, `cd`, pipes, redirects, shell operators, or any other command text. The cat path must point inside `{{ output_path(delivery, "") }}`; its path below that root is the workspace-relative output path.
{% elif delivery.name == "output" -%}
Emit each final file as a fenced block at the end of the final assistant message. Use `file:<relative-path>` for UTF-8 text and `file-base64:<relative-path>` for bytes. Put the file marker in the opening fence, not on a separate line. The fenced block body is the exact file content; do not JSON-escape it, summarize it, or replace it with preview text. Example:
```file:results.jsonl
{"ok": true}
```
{% endif -%}
